Encapsulation:
private variable ---> To set: setter methods[can set one value at a time], To get: getter methods
private variable ---> To set: Constructors[Can set multiple values at a time], To get get: getter methods
private variable ---> To set: Constructors[Can set multiple values at a time], Update the values of private variables: Setter Methods, To get get: getter methods

private methods within public method --> Encapsulation

Constructors are primarily used for initializing object attributes when the object is created,
while setter methods are used to modify variables values after the object has been instantiated.

API: Constructor ---> SET
     Setter      ---> UPDATE

     ==============================================================================
     USAGES OF 'this' KEYWORD:
     1. To differentiate between global variables and parameters name, if they are same, to call the global variable we use this keyword
     2. BUILDER PATTERN
     3. To call one  method inside of other method within same class
     4. To call one constructor inside of other Constructor [Note: Constructor calling has to be the first line of code inside other constructor]

     Call by Value and Call by Reference
     Call by Value: calling the methods by passing the value/s [arguments]
     CAll by Reference: calling the methods by passing the objects reference variable
                        This has an advantage of modifying the same object, using different objects reference variable/s

